Two men were left critically injured after they fell three storeys at a block of flats on Church Street in Pietermaritzburg.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement on Thursday that paramedics had arrived on the scene at 8.10pm to find two men lying in the parking area of the residence, surrounded by numerous members of the public.
"Paramedics assessed both men and found that both had sustained numerous injuries, leaving them in a critical condition."
READ: Teen makes ‘miraculous’ recovery after 15m fall
He said that the men had been treated for their injuries and provided with advanced life support interventions before they were transported to Edendale Provincial Hospital for urgent treatment.
"The details surrounding this incident are not yet known but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations."
In June this year, a 59-year-old man sustained fatal injuries when he apparently fell five storeys down a shaft at a building in Bloemfontein.
